The stanza has been pronounced an interpolation by Meineke and other erities, on the ground of its introduction of mythological lore, which seemed to thern frigid, and such as we find rather in Propertius and in the Alexandrine poets. Horace possibly had in mind the saying of Pyrrhus recorded by Florus, 1. 18 ‘Video me (inquit) plane Herculis sidere procreatum, cui quasi ab angue Lernaeo tot caesa hostium capita de sanguine suo renascantur.’
